<center><h1>VISSA</h1></center>

<TABLE>
<TR>
<TD valign="top"><IMG src="vissa-logo.jpg">
<TD valign="top">&nbsp &nbsp
<TD valign="top">

VISSA, (VIsualize Structure Sequence Alignment) is a program that 
can visualize both multiple seeuqnce alignment and 3D structure and
can also map residues from alignment onto 3D structure and vice versa. <P>

This program can help you with following analysis:
<UL>
<LI> Run, display, analyze multiple sequence alignment
<LI> Display 3D structure 
<LI> Map and highlight residues of interest from alignment onto 3D structure
<LI> Define structural site on 3D structure
<LI> Map structural sites on multiple sequence alignment
<LI> Make publication quality image
<LI> Many other analysis tools
</UL>
</TABLE>

<BR>
The program is written by 
      <A href="http://bioinformatics.burnham.org/liwz">Weizhong Li</A>, 
      <A href="mailto:liwz@sdsc.edu">liwz@sdsc.edu</A>
      at 
      <A href="http://bioinformatics.burnham.org">Adam Godzik's lab</a>


